lso insisted that their legal system serve the ends of justice and benefit the city and its people. In this way, the law ultimately satisfied most Athenians and probably produced just results as often as modern legal systems do. Comprehensive and wide-ranging, Democratic Law in Classical Athens offers a new perspective for viewing a legal system that was democratic in a way only the Athenians could achieve.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aDemocracyzGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aJustice, Administration of (Greek law) 0aJustice, Administration of (Greek law). 0aPublic law (Greek law) 0aPublic law (Greek law). 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32037240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477320389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781477320389.jpg  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK